CSC 407 Project
Ethan Engert and Ezra Nagel

To run:
    python -m venv .venv
    source .venv/bin/activate
    pip install -r requirements.txt

Create mysql database if not done already:
    mysql -u root -p
    
    CREATE DATABASE yellowbox_db;
    CREATE USER 'yellowbox_user'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';
    GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON yellowbox_db.* TO 'yellowbox_user'@'localhost';
    FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

Run Project:
    cd yellowbox
    python flasky.py

Import Tables:

    Powershell:
        Get-Content yellowbox_db.sql | mysql -u yellowbox_user -p yellowbox_db    
    Command Line:
        mysql -u yellowbox_user -p yellowbox_db < yellowbox_db.sql
        password: password

    Command for creating .sql file: 
        mysqldump -u yellowbox_user -p yellowbox_db > yellowbox_db.sql 

Example users:
    Range from 1-15, just replace number
    Username: user1
    Password: pass1


AWS/ Docker:
    
    mysql -h yellowbox-db.c12ociym6hbt.us-east-1.rds.amazonaws.com -u admin -p -P 3306 yellowbox_db < yellowbox_db.sql

    docker build -t flasky .

    docker run -p 5000:5000 flasky


ssh -i "yellowbox-key-pair.pem" ubuntu@ec2-54-146-181-208.compute-1.amazonaws.com
sudo apt update

generate token with read rights
git clone https://<USERNAME>:<TOKEN>@github.com/EzraNagel/CSC407.git

sudo apt install python3.12-venv
sudo python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

sudo apt install pkg-config libmysqlclient-dev
sudo apt install build-essential
sudo apt install python3.12-dev
pip install flask-wtf
pip install -r requirements.txt

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name ethanengert.com www.ethanengert.com;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000; # Forward requests to Flask app
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }

    # Optional: Redirect HTTP to HTTPS if you secure your site later
    # return 301 https://$host$request_uri;
}

